{"word":"G610 - ἀπόκριμα - apókrima - ap-ok'-ree-mah - Sentence","slug":"G610","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">ἀπόκριμα</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>apókrima"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>ap-ok'-ree-mah"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Sentence"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"- Original: <b><el>ἀπόκριμα</el></b> <p />- Transliteration: <b>Apokrima</b> <p />- Phonetic: <b>ap-ok'-ree-mah</b> <p class=\"def\">- Definition: </p> <p class='li260'><b>1.</b> an answer </p> <p class='li520'><b>a.</b> <a href='B:540 1:9'>2Co. 1:9</a> where the meaning is \"on asking myself whether I should come out safe from mortal peril, I answered 'I must Die'\" </p> <p class=\"origin\"/>- Origin: from <a href=\"#/G611\">G611</a> (in its original sense of judging) <p />- TDNT entry: 18:45,5 <p />- Part(s) of speech: Noun Neuter <p />- Strong's: From <a href=\"#/G611\">G611</a> (in its original sense of <i>judging</i>); a judicial <b><i>decision</i></b>: - sentence. "},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/G1252\">G1252</a>, <a href=\"#/G1253\">G1253</a>, <a href=\"#/G1469\">G1469</a>, <a href=\"#/G178\">G178</a>, <a href=\"#/G2631\">G2631</a>, <a href=\"#/G2632\">G2632</a>, <a href=\"#/G2633\">G2633</a>, <a href=\"#/G2917\">G2917</a>, <a href=\"#/G2919\">G2919</a>, <a href=\"#/G2920\">G2920</a>, <a href=\"#/G2922\">G2922</a>, <a href=\"#/G2923\">G2923</a>, <a href=\"#/G2924\">G2924</a>, <a href=\"#/G350\">G350</a>, <a href=\"#/G351\">G351</a>, <a href=\"#/G470\">G470</a>, <a href=\"#/G611\">G611</a>, <a href=\"#/G612\">G612</a>, <a href=\"#/G843\">G843</a>, <a href=\"#/G87\">G87</a>"}]}